args: I will stop their movement with my\nlightning, {player_name}!
Use that opening to shapeshift\nand annihilate them!
Come forth, lightning! Answer my call!
That's the last of them, Elly.
Boy, that was amazing! You two were\nin PERFECT sync with each other!
I don't deserve any of the credit.\nIt's all thanks to Albert.
And I believe the credit is yours.
Still, there is something I've noticed about\nyou in the time we've spent together.
Your true strength does not lie\nin your ability to shapeshift.
You carry justice in your heart—\nTHAT is your greatest strength.
No matter how much power you gain,\nyou will always walk the path of good.
Thank you for saying so, but I don't know\nif I'm special in that regard.
Oh, I disagree. There are many people\nin this world who allow power to steer\nthem toward terror and ruin.
A close friend of mine—or he used to be.
He was fascinated by the seeds' power\njust like my father, and ended up stealing\none from the kingdom's storehouse.
So HE has the seed you're looking for?
That's right—although he does not possess\nit in the sense you are thinking of.
Rather, he allowed the seed to absorb him\nand became a fiend of his own free will.
Do you intend to fight him?
If I wish to destroy the seed,\nI have no choice.
I must be the one to end this.
As his former friend and leader, I have a\nduty to atone for his mistakes—even if it\ncomes at the cost of my life.
There is one thing I can't help\nbut wonder, however.
If I take the life of both my father and my\nfriend, will I still be the man I am now?
...Heh. Perhaps I have more hesitations\nabout this plan than I first thought.
And there's nothing wrong with that.
You're going to battle your friend—\nit would be odd if you DIDN'T hesitate.
I'm relieved to hear you say as much.
I know I've had my fair share of doubts\nover the months.
But my friends accepted me despite that,\nand it's allowed me to grow stronger.
So stay and become stronger with us.
(Accepting myself as I am,\ndoubts and all...)
(All this time, I've thought of nothing but\nfulfilling my duty while lying to myself\nabout my true feelings.)
(But perhaps accepting my hesitations\nis true strength, in the end.)
